establish confidence) and wonders why it's bigger, letting me get the
old one I had from disaster motor, with complementary brushes, so I get
to take the engine out and replace that soon too (not like I don't have
to for nearly wasted heads) With a 905 and 1 shim, still slightly loose,
unless brandy new, like 100 miles. This caused havoc, and on top of my
imbalanced compression (due to heads that were flycut differently I
imagine, since although I requested new, when I bought this motor, I got
"low mile" ones, that already nuked a valve spring on me, and spec at
two different compression ratios. A 900mm belt with 5 shims is almost
perfect (rest of shims outside of course), and pulls the generator
nicely. I think this motor DID stretch valves though, and am monitoring
the condition closely. I doubt this engine will last long. Nice to jump
in the 98k OE mile Ghia, returned almost to bone stock, and have it
purr, and pay some f-up 1700 bucks plus core to screw around with me. I
demanded new heads be sent to me, or rebuilt ones with good parts and
cced in at least one cyl each to prove they are close. Let's see what
support I get 10 months and 1200 miles later. Hope he does, because I
